reau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%20published%20real%20GDP%20data%20for%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%202025%20on%20Wednesday.%3Cp%3ELiao%20Pan%2FChina%20News%20Service%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EReal%20GDP%20increased%20at%20an%20annualized%20rate%20of%203%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%2C%20more%20than%20expected.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThat%20reverses%20the%20shrinking%20economy%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20but%20tariffs%20cloud%20future%20performance.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20report%20is%20just%20one%20of%20several%20this%20week%20that%20highlight%20how%20the%20economy%20is%20doing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20real%20gross%20domestic%20product%20grew%20at%20an%20annualized%20rate%20of%203%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%2C%20surpassing%20the%20forecast%20of%202.5%25%20and%20a%20sharp%20rebound%20from%20the%20first%20quarter's%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompared%20to%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20the%20upturn%20in%20real%20GDP%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20primarily%20reflected%20a%20downturn%20in%20imports%20and%20an%20acceleration%20in%20consumer%20spending%20that%20were%20partly%20offset%20by%20a%20downturn%20in%20investment%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FSwE6Z%2F5%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Change%20in%20real%20GDP%20from%20previous%20quarter%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22482%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EReal%20personal%20consumer%20spending%20rose%201.4%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%2C%20surpassing%20the%200.5%25%20increase%20in%20the%20first.%20Fixed%20investment%20rose%20just%200.4%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20after%20a%207.6%25%20increase%20in%20the%20first%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%2037.9%25%20increase%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20imports%20fell%2030.3%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20as%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20tariff%20push%20heated%20up.%20Imports%20are%20subtracted%20in%20the%20GDP%20calculation.%20Exports%20fell%201.8%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%2C%20after%20a%200.4%25%20rise%20in%20the%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20consumer%20has%20been%20resilient%20despite%20recent%20volatility%20and%20policy%20uncertainty%2C%20and%20any%20employment%20weakness%20will%20be%20viewed%20as%20a%20bellwether%20for%20weakening%20consumption%2C%20which%20would%20likely%20push%20the%20Fed%20to%20resume%20cutting%20rates%20sooner%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ryan%20Weldon%2C%20investment%20director%20and%20portfolio%20manager%20at%20IFM%20Investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20releases%20beyond%20Wednesday's%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%20report%20indicate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finvestors-economic-optimism-no-recession-jobs-report-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehow%20the%20economy%20is%20doing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Federal%20Reserve's%20Beige%20Book%20covering%20economic%20conditions%20between%20late%20May%20and%20early%20July%20said%20five%20of%20the%2012%20Fed%20districts%20had%20slight%20or%20modest%20economic%20gains%20and%20another%20five%20reported%20flat%20activity%2C%20compared%20to%20three%20with%20slight%20economic%20growth%20and%20three%20with%20no%20change%20in%20activity%20in%20the%20previous%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Beige%20Book%20also%20said%20there%20was%20a%20slight%20improvement%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-navigate-toughest-job-market-apply-for-jobs-last-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemployment%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Analysts%20and%20economists%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20labor%20market%20is%20good%20if%20you%20have%20a%20job%2C%20and%20is%20not%20so%20great%20if%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%